  "title": "CONSTRUCTION SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead the Practice team in development, configuration and implementation of the firm’s Practice Management System</li><li>Organise and review meetings</li><li>Oversee and supervise the Practice Management team in providing support to internal teams</li><li>Lead and provide guidance during review meetings</li><li>Consolidate and provide weekly progress updates to the core Project Team</li><li>Monitor and manage vendor’s progress in fulfilling deliverables and meeting timelines</li><li>Support Project Lead in tracking implementation progress, monitoring customisation budget and preparing information for meetings with vendor</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>At least 6 years’ experience in a site supervisor role, preferably from the professional services, consulting or financial services industry</li><li>Project management experience in enterprise business management solutions is advantageous</li><li>Tertiary qualifications in finance, accounting or a related discipline</li><li>Strong verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Flexible and able to work collaboratively within a team environment</li><li>Ability to multi-task, prioritise and work effectively under time pressure</li></ul>",
